        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "SQA acceptance criteria for MRL 5 CFD hemolysis solver",
        "description": "Solver must be under formal version control with traceable release history; regression test suite must cover all physics modules used in hemolysis prediction; post-processing scripts must have documented unit tests. Achieved Gradation 4 satisfies MRL 5 requirement."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Code verification was performed using the method of manufactured solutions (MMS) for the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver and the power-law hemolysis transport equation. Observed convergence rates match theoretical second-order accuracy (p=1.97 for velocity, p=1.94 for hemolysis scalar). All MMS tests pass with errors below 0.1% at the production mesh resolution.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/code-verification",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Code verification acceptance criteria",
        "description": "MMS-based convergence order must be within 5% of theoretical order for all governing equations. Hemolysis transport scalar must demonstrate second-order convergence. All MMS residuals must be below 0.5% at production resolution."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted on the FDA centrifugal pump geometry (coarse: 2.1M cells, medium: 5.8M cells, fine: 14.2M cells). Grid convergence index (GCI) computed per Celik et al. (2008): GCI_fine = 1.4% for NIH, 1.8% for mean impeller velocity. Monotonic convergence confirmed. Temporal discretization verified with three time-step levels; temporal GCI < 0.8%. Production simulation uses fine mesh with adaptive time-stepping.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/discretization-error",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "GCI on NIH quantity of interest must be below 5% on the fine mesh. Monotonic convergence must be demonstrated across all three mesh levels. Temporal GCI must be below 2%."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions for the FDA pump benchmark are thoroughly documented: fluid properties (bovine blood analog, viscosity 3.5 mPa·s at 37°C), inlet flow rates (2.5, 3.5, 4.5, 5.5, 6.0 L/min), impeller speeds (2500, 3000, 3500 RPM), and temperature control (37±0.5°C). All five operating points used in validation are within the documented test envelope. Traceability from raw experimental records to published dataset is confirmed.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/test-conditions",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria",
        "description": "All experimental boundary conditions must be documented with measurement uncertainty. Fluid properties must be traceable to calibrated instruments. Operating points must span the COU envelope."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison of CFD-predicted NIH against experimental measurements performed at all five operating points using the validation metric of Oberkampf and Barone. Normalized prediction error ranges from 3.2% to 12.1% across operating conditions, with mean error 8.3%. Experimental measurement uncertainty (±6.5% NIH from inter-laboratory variability) is explicitly included in the comparison. All predicted values fall within the combined simulation-experiment uncertainty band.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/output-comparison",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Quantitative validation metric must be reported with both simulation and experimental uncertainty. Prediction errors must be within combined uncertainty band at all operating points. Comparison must be performed at the primary QoI (NIH) rather than surrogate quantities."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "The primary quantity of interest is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH), which directly corresponds to the clinical endpoint of red blood cell destruction. NIH is the regulatory-accepted metric per FDA guidance on blood-contacting devices. The model directly predicts NIH via the power-law hemolysis model integrated over Lagrangian particle trajectories; no surrogate mapping is required. QoI relevance is rated Gradation 4.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/qoi-relevance",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The simulated QoI must directly map to the clinical/regulatory endpoint without intermediate surrogate transformation. NIH must be computed from the simulation output using the accepted power-law formulation."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Validation activities use the FDA generic centrifugal pump, which shares impeller topology, operating Reynolds number range (Re 2800–8400), and blood-analog fluid with the target VAD device. Operating conditions in the validation set (2.5–6 L/min, 2500–3500 RPM) overlap with all five COU operating points. Geometric similarity is quantified: impeller diameter ratio 0.94, blade count identical, volute aspect ratio within 8%. Validation relevance is rated Gradation 4.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/validation-relevance",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Validation activity relevance acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Validation geometry must be geometrically similar to COU device. Operating conditions in validation must overlap with COU envelope. Fluid properties must match within documented tolerance. Geometric similarity metrics must be reported."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence of the SIMPLE pressure-velocity coupling algorithm is verified at each time step: all residuals (continuity, momentum, hemolysis scalar) converge to below 1×10⁻⁶. Round-off error assessed by comparison of double- and extended-precision runs; difference in NIH < 0.02%. Solver floating-point arithmetic verified against IEEE 754 compliance documentation for the target HPC platform.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/solver-error",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical solver error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Iterative residuals must reach below 1e-5 for all transported quantities. Round-off error contribution to QoI must be below 0.1%. Solver must be IEEE 754 compliant on target hardware."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Simulation setup was performed by a credentialed CFD engineer with 8 years of blood pump simulation experience. An independent peer review of boundary condition assignments, mesh quality metrics, and post-processing scripts was conducted by a second engineer. Checklist-based review protocol documented 47 setup parameters; all reviewed and signed off. No use errors identified during review. Gradation 3 achieved.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
