      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "The FDA pump benchmark dataset includes measurements from three independent laboratories, providing n=15 NIH measurements per operating point (5 replicates per lab). Sample size is sufficient to characterize inter-laboratory variability (CV=6.5%) and compute 95% confidence intervals on experimental NIH. Sample representativeness is confirmed by checking that all samples used blood analog fluid within ±3% of target viscosity. Gradation 3 achieved.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/test-samples",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test samples acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Experimental dataset must include replicate measurements sufficient to characterize measurement variability. Inter-laboratory or inter-run variability must be quantified. Sample fluid properties must be verified against target specifications."
      }
